gaṃdhadviṣa</span> <span>q. v.</span>). <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div> 3 <span>N.</span> of the elephant of Indra. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div> 4 <span>N.</span> of Gaṇeśa. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>—</strong> <span class='sdata'>nartaḥ</span> a kind of bird, the wagtail <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>—</strong> <span class='sdata'>puṣpa</span> <i><span>a.</span></i> everflowering. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>—</strong> <span class='sdata'>(ṣpaḥ)</span> the cocoa-nut tree. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>—</strong> <span class='sdata'>prasūnaḥ</span> <span>N.</span> of various plants:- <span class='sdata'>sohita, arka</span> and <span class='sdata'>kuṃda</span>. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>—</strong> <span class='sdata'>phala</span> <i><span>a.</span></i> always bearing fruit. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>—</strong> <span class='sdata'>(laḥ)</span> <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div> 1 the Bilva tree. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div> 2 the jack tree. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div> 3 the glomerous fig-tree. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div> 4 the cocoanut tree. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>—</strong> <span class='sdata'>bhavya</span> <i><span>a.</span></i> always present. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>—</strong> <span class='sdata'>yogin</span> <i><span>m.</span></i> an epithet of Kṛṣṇa. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>—</strong> <span class='sdata'>śivaḥ</span> <span>N.</span> of Śiva.","evidence":{"band":1,"band_label":"core -- memorise","rank_all":189,"count_all":2946,"first_era":"Vedic","genre":null,"example":{"sa":"sadā","ru":"всегда","work":"01_mahabharata-adiparva","passage":"1.1.148-156","kind":"translation","source":"corpus_lexicon.jsonl (pwg_ru Phase 4, SanskritLexicography/RussianTranslation)"},"b